<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#D0BC90">Originally posted by Witterquick on 10-28-2002 05:44 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I really only have a minor complaint about the game overall.  I feel that some quests might have been restricted by level and not just, say, reputation.  I know it seems most folks here like the open-endedness and the experimentation but it's frustrating at times to be given a quest you have no hope of finishing at your current level only to travel across the world in search of your goal and to be crushed outright upon arriving.  Level restrictions ("I'd ask you to help but I'm afraid you just don't seem up to the challenge just yet.") would alleviate this.  Let the level range be fairly broad so that it's still possible if you pick up the quest on the early end it'll be tough but not impossible with proper tactics.

Otherwise, to paraphrase a review I read somewhere this is the game I wish Diablo II had been.  Yes, it is fairly challenging early on and even though I've only made my way to level 19 I've had a huge amount of fun in a world that really seems to be alive.  I feel that with food and alchemy thrown in there's just about enough healing but not so much that you're leaving potions lying around as you're too lazy to pick them up.  I'm currently a warrior who has focused almost exclusively on warrior skills but with a few rogue skills thrown in and of course the Restoration spell.  It seems to me you really can make the class you want to play with this system and this is just about the most fun I've had in ages.</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
